SIMPLE: immoral
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immoral
<hw>Im*mor"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>moral</ets>: cf. F. <ets>immoral</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Not moral; inconsistent with rectitude, purity, or good morals;
contrary to conscience or the divine law; wicked; unjust; dishonest;
vicious; licentious; <as>as, an <ex>immoral</ex> man; an
<ex>immoral</ex> deed.</as></def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Wicked; sinful; criminal; vicious; unjust;
dishonest; depraved; impure; unchaste; profligate; dissolute; abandoned;
licentious; lewd; obscene.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immorality</ent>⟦br⟧
